s will ask guests to fill out a small form inquiring about the service provided, and what you did and didn t like about your visit."]},"id":"bbfa0d9e-72ac-409d-ad58-4b61c28eff11","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Major Corporations"},"id":"fad20b95-994f-4b02-8fdb-fabe1eba7c89","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["All major companies like Kraft, Kellogg, Dove, etc. use focus groups and surveys to determine consumer trends. Focus groups and surveys go hand and hand. Surveyors ask questions about what kind of products you buy and how much you are willing to spend. This gives companies an idea about where their target market is and how much the average person is willing to spend on products. All new products put on the market go through some kind of consumer focus group."]},"id":"96c723d7-62ab-4ad4-b769-97e831c36b01","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Entertainment"},"id":"62772d6b-d6bc-40f1-8097-cefe629f92c2","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["No movie or television show is released before it goes through a focus group. These are called screenings. In a screening production, studios show a focus group a new movie or TV show then ask them questions about what they thought of these programs. Many studios will take the public s opinion into account and adjust a program accordingly depending on the audience they are trying to reach. If the studio is screening a children s show, and the focus group of parents say they would not let their children watch that program, it s safe to assume the show will not go on the air without major rewrites.<br/><br/>"]},"id":"7888f871-7c5d-4d96-849d-7a2f9cb7a3d9","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Politics"},"id":"3bff8b52-60c7-4c48-adc6-c6d39e1b7eb8","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Political surveys become more prevalent in election years. Pollsters try to predict the outcome of political races by conducting surveys or polls. They will often target people in specific groups like party affiliations, minorities or income levels to determine which candidate will win.<br/><br/>"]},"id":"ded1f8e9-26f6-4070-9d63-2d416fe0fa4e","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"So What s the Point?"},"id":"0ab8e5fc-5499-4057-8ecb-7e8a55e541a8","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Surveys are a complicated way to create simple answers. The general public doesn t want to know how the evening news acquired the information they just want to know the numbers about presidential approval ratings, or what percentage of high income families go to McDonalds. Surveys are a complicated, behind the scenes process that affect our everyday lives, we just don t realize it."]},"id":"d0077649-fb65-4eec-bdaa-e9ab6dac391d","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"article_page_626","url":"/surveys-and-everyday-life","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"erin-monaghan","url":"/author/erin-monaghan","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Erin Monaghan","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"pJhSzFvAjtB92wXxfULoVW","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"1970-01-01T00:00:00Z","datePublished":"2014-08-12T14:22:05Z","name":"Surveys and Everyday Life","synopsis":"We have all gotten phone calls at dinnertime, shanghaied at the mall or answered a few questions online, all in the name of public opinion.","review":{},"strapline":"We have all gotten phone calls at dinnertime, shanghaied at the mall or answered a few questions online, all in the name of public opinion.","language":"en","dateModified":"2014-08-12T14:22:05Z","id":"mJUVtyJjYdTuvfjJexUvfN","meta":{"title":"Surveys and Everyday Life","description":"We have all gotten phone calls at dinnertime, shanghaied at the mall or answered a few questions online, all in the name of public opinion. In fact, it seems everywhere we turn there is a new"},"products":[],"dateImported":"2019-04-17T20:49:33Z","type":"feature","template":"standard","social":{"twitter":{"image":{"status":"","height":0,"path":"/mwtVrCWPE3FtbZ8AUc7ij5.jpg